window.cpp: constructor - WindowHints make the window undrawable. (Check what why and if I can use them.)
window.cpp: Run - instead of creating a callback, we check it manaully. Maybe make a Channel class to send from the callback to the X object (as generic as possible).

UICommand queue in Window - OpenGL functions need to be called on the same thread as the window, thus we need a functions queue in the window that needs to be executed after rendering all widgets.


